  "title": "Step 3: In , create the peering connection.",
  "description": "Atlas supports network peering\nconnections for dedicated clusters hosted on AWS (Amazon Web Services), Google Cloud, and\nAzure (Microsoft Azure), and on multi-cloud sharded clusters. Network peering establishes a private\nconnection between your Atlas VPC (Virtual Private Cloud) and your cloud provider's\nVPC (Virtual Private Cloud). The connection isolates traffic from public networks for added\nsecurity.",
